drawing-codec-libredwg-submodule — how clautolisp reads/writes DWG
==================================================================

Parent: drawing-database-api.issue (Phase 17e).
Depends on: Phase 17b (CL drawing API), Phase 17c (DXF codec).

Context
-------

The drawing database (drawing-database-api.issue) needs a DWG
codec. DWG is proprietary, binary, and version-stamped (R12 /
R2000 / R2004 / R2007 / R2010 / R2013 / R2018 …) with no Autodesk
specification. Writing one from scratch is out of the question;
the practical open implementation is GNU libredwg (LGPL), which
reads and writes DWG, carries an in-memory object model, and ships
DXF and JSON emitters.

DXF lands first (Phase 17c) because it is documented, pure-CL, and
maps almost 1:1 onto the group-code lists already stored. This
issue is only the DWG step on top of it.

Decisions (made 2026-06)
------------------------

  1. **Integration mechanism: vendored git submodule + CFFI.**
     libredwg is vendored as a git submodule pinned to a chosen
     release, *built by us* from source, and linked via CFFI. We do
     NOT depend on a package-manager build of libredwg: we want to
     pin the exact release, carry a maintenance branch if we hit
     bugs, and control building/packaging. (The shell-out-to-CLI
     path was considered and rejected for the production codec.)
     - Submodule: ~clautolisp/third-party/libredwg~, pinned at tag
       **0.13.3** (commit 443163b…).
     - Build *toolchain* (autoconf/automake/libtool) is a generic
       developer prerequisite, NOT the dependency — it may come from
       any package manager; only libredwg itself is vendored.

  2. **Submodule placement + build.** Submodule under
     ~clautolisp/third-party/libredwg~. A Makefile target builds it
     in place (autogen.sh → configure → make) producing the shared
     library; the optional ~clautolisp/drawing-dwg~ ASDF system
     loads that library via CFFI and registers the ~:dwg~ codec.
     The DWG system is *optional* and NOT part of the core
     ~clautolisp~ aggregate, so the core build/test stays green
     where libredwg is absent (the drawing layer already signals
     ~drawing-format-error~ for ~:dwg~ until a codec registers).
     CI: a dedicated lane builds the submodule then runs the
     ~clautolisp/drawing-dwg/tests~ system.

  3. **CFFI surface (minimal, header-driven).** Rather than bind
     libredwg's entire Dwg_Data object model, bind the small stable
     surface needed to bridge to the Phase-17c DXF codec
     in-process: read a DWG into Dwg_Data and emit DXF (and the
     reverse), then reuse READ/WRITE-DRAWING's DXF path. Exact
     entry points to be chosen after reading the vendored headers
     (dwg.h / dwg_api.h). This keeps the binding small and robust
     across libredwg versions.

  4. **Version coverage.** Whatever the pinned libredwg release
     supports (R13–R2018 per its matrix); documented once bindings
     land.

  5. **Licensing.** libredwg is GPL-3.0; clautolisp is AGPL-3.0
     (COPYING) — compatible. Vendoring + linking is fine under the
     (A)GPL; record this once the build lands.

In scope
--------

  - `clautolisp.drawing.libredwg` implementing read-drawing /
    write-drawing for DWG behind the format dispatch.
  - Submodule + build/CI wiring.
  - Round-trip tests against a DWG fixture corpus (load DWG ->
    drawing -> write DWG -> reload, compare).

Out of scope
------------

  - A native-Lisp DWG codec.
  - DWG versions outside libredwg's supported matrix.

Acceptance criteria
-------------------

  - `read-drawing "foo.dwg"` and `write-drawing d "foo.dwg"` work
    for the claimed version subset.
  - DWG round-trip fidelity tests pass in CI on at least one lane.
  - The licence note in the issue is resolved and recorded.

* Resolution (triage 2026-07-23)

Shipped (Phase 17e): pinned libredwg 0.13.3 submodule, CFFI shim clal_dwg.c, dwg-read/write-drawing in drawing-dwg/source/codec.lisp, tests + CI lanes + the Windows DLL shim (1.2.3).
